Citation.sTitle: Effect of temperature on the volumetric properties of dilute  aqueous solutions of 1,2-hexanediol, 1,5-hexanediol,  1,6-hexanediol, and 2,5-hexanediol
Citation.sAbstract: Excess molar volumes V E  m and partial molar volumes V 2 have been determined from density measurements for dilute aqueous solutions  of 1,2-hexanediol, 1,5-hexanediol, 1,6-hexanediol, and 2,5-hexanediol at (283.15, 288.15, 293.15, 298.15, 303.15, and 308.15) K as a  function of composition. The infinite dilution partial molar volumes V12  of alcohols in aqueous solution are evaluated through extrapolation.  Interactions of the different solutes with water are discussed in terms of the effect of the position of the hydroxyl groups in the  hexanediol molecule. The limiting slope of the partial molar volumes is interpreted in terms of alkanediol hydration.
